          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1634028571344-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1634028571344-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chilli</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Combine your <strong>peanut butter</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> in a bowl and mix well until you have a smooth paste</p><p>Add your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>,<strong> rice vinegar</strong>,<strong> chopped chilli</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and mix well to combine – this is your <strong>peanut dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1634028580292-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1634028580292-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1634028580292-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1634028580292-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1634028580292-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once warmed through, reduce the heat to medium-low and sprinkle your<strong> five-spice</strong> over the meat-free chick'n</p><p>Give everything a good mix up until the meat-free chick'n is evenly coated in the spice and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1634028584240-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1634028584240-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1634028584240-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1634028584240-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1634028584240-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>cooked meat-free chick'n</strong> to a clean board and shred apart using two forks – this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Once shredded, season the<strong> pulled meat-free chick'n</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>bang bang meat-free chick'n</strong></p><p>Fluff the <strong>cooked rice</strong> with a fork and add it to the <strong>crunchy salad</strong> – this is your <strong>crunchy rice salad</strong></p><p>Toss the <strong>crunchy rice salad</strong> in a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and season with a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1634028588633-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1634028588633-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1634028588633-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1634028588633-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1634028588633-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> bang bang meat-free chick'n</strong> over the <strong>crunchy rice salad </strong>and drizzle the <strong>peanut dressing</strong> all over – this is your<strong> bang bang meat-free chick'n with crunchy rice salad</strong></p><p>Garnish with a sprinkling of <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
